# EventHub — REST API test requests
# Use with the VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
# Make sure the server is running: npm run dev

@base = http://localhost:3000/api

### ─── EVENTS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all events (public)
GET {{base}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Get a single event by ID (replace ID below after running GET all events)
GET {{base}}/events/REPLACE_WITH_EVENT_ID
Content-Type: application/json

###

### Create a new event (admin only — you must be logged in as admin via the browser first,
###   or use a tool that shares session cookies, e.g. REST Client with cookie support)
POST {{base}}/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "API Test Event",
  "description": "Created via REST Client for testing purposes.",
  "category": "Workshop",
  "date": "2026-10-10",
  "time": "09:00",
  "location": "Online",
  "price": 0,
  "capacity": 100
}

###

### Update an event (admin only)
PUT {{base}}/events/REPLACE_WITH_EVENT_ID
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Event Title",
  "price": 500
}

###

### Delete an event (admin only)
DELETE {{base}}/events/REPLACE_WITH_EVENT_ID
Content-Type: application/json

###

### ─── BOOKINGS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get bookings (user sees their own; admin sees all — requires active session)
GET {{base}}/bookings
Content-Type: application/json

###

### ─── CONTACTS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Get all enquiries (admin only — requires active session)
GET {{base}}/contacts
Content-Type: application/json

###
